    {
      "id": "el_100",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 535,
      "y": 2708,
      "width": 296,
      "height": 202,
      "text": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: Man sees goods train pass him\n  Man=point, Opposite→Rel=50+40=90=25 m/s\nStep 2: L = Rel×T = 25×9 = 225m\n\nTRICK:\nMan in train = moving point observer\nL = (S1+S2)×T in m/s\n= (90×5/18)×9 = 25×9 = 225m\n\n  ──→ Man's train     ←── Goods train\n       50 km/h            40 km/h\n\nAnswer: 225m ✓",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 12,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 10000,
