      "groupIds": [
        "type_17"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LOGIC:\nStep 1: Man sees goods train pass him\n  Man=point, Opposite→Rel=50+40=90=25 m/s\nStep 2: L = Rel×T = 25×9 = 225m\n\nTRICK:\nMan in train = moving point observer\nL = (S1+S2)×T in m/s\n= (90×5/18)×9 = 25×9 = 225m\n\n  ──→ Man's train     ←── Goods train\n       50 km/h            40 km/h\n\nAnswer: 225m ✓",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
